body_html:
Do you read multiple times from the same index?

On Nov 13, 2016 6:23 PM, "s4sarath" notifications@github.com wrote:

https://github.com/ebrevdo

@ebrevdo https://github.com/ebrevdo @aselle https://github.com/aselle

  • Without passing tensor array name as arguments also , I am getting the
    same error . Tensor array name was more of a debugging mode for me , to
    understand which Tensor array is causing the error . AlreadyExistsError:
    Resource _tensor_arrays/while/TensorArray_6/N10tensorflow11TensorArrayE

The tensorflow version was 0.9

I upgraded it to 0.11 . Now the error has changed .
InvalidArgumentError: TensorArray while/TensorArray_6_3: Could not read
from TensorArray index 0 because it has not yet been written to.
How come this error is happening , if we are properly writing it in each
iteration. Please have a look .
